 ('21', '23', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '4vTQElr4-hM', '<p>\r\n	 <a href=\"http://www.missionog.com/people/andrew-newcomb/\" target=\"_blank\">Andy Newcomb</a> is a technology operator and investor with a history of start-up innovation, successful team leadership, and financial achievement. At <a href=\"http://www.missionog.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MissionOG</a> Andy works with partner companies on market analysis, sales strategies, and client delivery and management.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	     Previously, Andy co-founded Relay Network, a mobile communications company; was Group Head of Sales and Corporate Development for Citi Prepaid Services; and was a founding team member of Ecount (acquired by Citi), a pioneer and leader in the prepaid card industry. Preceding Ecount, Andy spent eight years in investment management, most recently as a portfolio manager with Chartwell Investment Partners where his teams achieved top decile and quartile rankings.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	     Andy serves as a board member of portfolio company <a href=\"http://peoplelinx.com/\" target=\"_blank\">PeopleLinx</a>, and on the boards of Softgate Systems, RewardsNOW and OneTwoSee. Andy graduated from Trinity College with a B.A. in History.\r\n</p>', 'Listen, Peel & Pain', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2013-09-12 17:20:57', '2014-06-11 20:41:45', '9b46f73e-bbb1-422a-ae41-f67f9b400f3b'),
 ('22', '24', 'en_us', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'XaSBhV3FvyA', '<p>\r\n	           In 1990 <a href=\"http://dansko.com/About%20Dansko/\">Mandy Cabot</a> and her husband Peter Kjellerup co-founded <a href=\"http://dansko.com/\">Dansko</a>, a leader in innovative comfort footwear. Since the discovery of their first product in a tiny store in Denmark, Dansko (literally translated as \"Danish shoe\") now generates annual sales of over $150 million. Today their offering includes sandals, boots, heels, flats, healthcare apparel and many types of clogs. In 2012, Mandy and Peter redeemed all of their shares in Dansko to form a new ESOP (Employee Stock Ownership Plan), resulting in 100% employee ownership.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	     Under Mandy and Peter\'s leadership, Dansko has joined the ranks of companies achieving the \"Inc 500 List\" of fastest growing private companies and the Philadelphia Inquirer\'s \"Top Workplaces List\" of best places to work. Dansko is also the winner the Paradigm Award from the Chester County Development Council; the Leadership Award from the Delaware Valley Green Building Council; the Triple Bottom Line Award from the Social Business Network of Greater Philadelphia; and seven time winner of the Footwear Plus Award for Design Excellence in Women\'s Comfort. A founding B Corporation, Dansko operates out of its LEED Certified headquarters in Chester County, PA.\r\n</p>', 'Crisis of Confidence', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2013-09-12 21:08:11', '2014-05-14 01:47:39', 'a8f46acb-feac-41ad-b686-fcb1ba4de531'),
